{
  "stem": "19895.8",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, irony of life, that's while the Russians freed me, and I am very thankful that I happened to be on their way to beat the Third Reich, and they gave back my life and freedom.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But on the other hand, the system during Communism has somewhat took away my enthusiasm to live under the system forever.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when the revolution broke out, I escaped from the country, from Hungary, and-- and crossed the border over to Austria.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then I have made contact with different relief organizations, as well as some relatives in the United States.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in a few months, two months exactly, my time was two months to live in Vienna when I was cleared all the papers to enter the United States as an immigrant.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I left my parents behind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was very difficult for me, because again, we were separated, not knowing that the Iron Curtain will eventually lift and how do we see each other again.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I have entered the United States.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had difficulty with the English language.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had some high school English, but it was far from being conversational.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a rebirth.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a rebirth because I chose this country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I arrived here on my own choice to be in this country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It happens to be so that I arrived on my birthday, on February the 11th.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I-- I was very interested in seeing America.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I was stationed in Camp Kilmer, which is in New Jersey.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's a location where the American military forces were gathered before they went over to Europe on the Liberty ships to go to Europe, transports.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
